content: This contribution hasn’t received enough positive votes from the community. The "REVERSE" option has therefore been deactivated.

For what it's worth, I couldn't do anything in 15 minutes.
Maybe I could have solved it by brute force, but I didn't expect I'd be able to, so I was trying to iterate through all arrangements of the numbers.
It is indeed an interesting puzzle, but it is on the difficult side for Clash of Code.

Comment: Really like the idea but you should explain how the numbers work more clearly.
I also agree that this is not fit for reverse mode.
Finally I think the concept is a bit hard to implement for a 5 minute time span

The first test case is the same as the validator.

I would not recommend for reverse mode, since I would not expect anyone multiplying quickly 2-3 or more digit numbers just looking at them.

For shortest and fastest looks fine.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: I love it

Isn't it very similar to this one ?
https://www.codingame.com/contribute/view/564753936ccb225119beb59d7db17d919251

Well... Similar, but not the same, That is very restricted to 4 character length solutions, also it's a puzzle. But correct, I was not aware of that puzzle. 
For this, you need a bit more skill I think.

I don't think reverse is harder, I actually think reverse is easier, because you can immediately make the connection of the numbers and the multiplication, without reading the task.
As of 5 minutes... I'm not an expert, but usually around my level, I got Clashes which takes almost 15 minutes for all my seniors to do, and this is clearly much-much simpler, because it is basically just a "what are your divisors" question, with some ifs at the end, doing from scratch, without overthinking. So mos def not hitting the 10 minute mark.

I can explain it more clearly in the text, that is a valid point.

In my opinion, it depends. People with strong math background will have at least 3-4 algos in their head to get fast factors, and there are hundreds of Clashes using similar rhings. The only difference here is that this Clash adds a twist, so it is not just 45 second for somebody, but they actually need some thinking to how to actually do it.
I get it, that it is harder than many of the clashes, but sadly when I do an easy one, the moderators rejecting them for being too easy :)
anyway its a damn crazy question i love it thanks for this awesome problem
